Skinny Chicken Parmesan with Edemame Pasta

1-1 1/2 lbs chicken breast, halved or thinly sliced
2 egg whites
1/2 c bread crumbs **
1/4 c shredded parmesan + 6 tbsp for chicken topping
3/4 c marinara sauce + more for serving over pasta
7.05oz package edemame spaghetti prepared per package instructions

Preheat oven to 450F and prepare a large baking dish with non-stick cooking spray. Put egg whites in shallow dish. Mix bread crumbs and parmesan in a second shallow dish. Coat each side of chicken in egg, then coat with bread crumb mixture. Place each chicken breast in baking dish. Bake for 18 min. Top with ~2 tbsp marinara and 1 tbsp parmesan cheese; bake until bubbly, ~5min. Serve over pasta.

**seasoned (gluten-free) crouton crumbs - if not using preseasoned, add some like garlic powder, italian seasoning, etc.

Marinara Sauce

2 tbsp evoo
1 medium onion, chopped
4 cloves garlic, finely chopped
6oz can tomato paste no salt added
1/4 c red wine (optional)
2x28oz crushed tomatoes
1 tsp sea salt + more to taste
1/4 tsp ground pepper

Heat oil in large saucepan over medium high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring frequently, for 5-6 min or until onion is soft. Add garlic and tomato paste; cook, stirring constantly for 1 min. Add wine; cook, stirring constantly for 1 min. Add tomatoes, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Reduce heat to low, gently boil, stirring occasionally for 1 hr.

note: can cook on very low for up to 6 hrs, may need to add 1/4 c water or broth as needed for desired consistency.
